Reasoning: The paper discusses sublinear-time approximation algorithms for optimization problems in machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper specifically mentions optimization problems arising in machine learning. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses novel sampling techniques and a new multiplicative update algorithm. cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper mentions lower bounds on running times. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possibility as the paper discusses kernelized versions of the optimization problems. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possibility as the paper discusses lower bounds on running times and the unit-cost RAM model.
